# PeerJS broker configuration.
#
# Leave these unset to use the public `0.peerjs.com` cloud broker (the default).
# That broker is rate-limited and can temporarily IP-ban heavy testers
# (Cloudflare error 1015), which makes the server list and room codes disappear.
#
# To run your own broker instead (no rate limit), start one with:
#   npm run peerserver            # listens on :9000, path /
# then copy this file to `.env.local`, uncomment, and restart `npm run dev`.
#
# For two machines on a LAN, set VITE_PEER_HOST to the broker host's LAN IP
# (e.g. 192.168.1.50) and make sure port 9000 is reachable.

# VITE_PEER_HOST=localhost
# VITE_PEER_PORT=9000
# VITE_PEER_PATH=/
# VITE_PEER_SECURE=false
# VITE_PEER_KEY=peerjs
